- `makeConnectionDescriptor` → `makeRackConnection` (line 467 - calling external API)\n\n### Hard Constraints\n- **Owned files only** - no touching Worker A/B/D/E files\n- **No shell file renames** - Worker D owns rack_node_shell → rack_module_shell\n- **No midisynth.lua** - Worker E owns that\n- **No builds** - no cmake, ninja, standalone, VST\n- **Verification only** via `luac -p`, `rg`, safe python\n\n### Unresolved Dependencies (External APIs I Call)\n| Symbol | Owner | Location in My Files |\n|--------|-------|---------------------|\n| `MidiSynthRackSpecs.spliceNode()` | Worker B | `rack_wire_layer.lua:608,618` |\n| `RackLayout.cloneNodes()` | Worker A | `patchbay_runtime.lua:285,320` |\n| `RackLayout.findNodeIndex()` | Worker A | `patchbay_runtime.lua:286` |\n| `RackLayout.makeConnectionDescriptor()` | Worker A | `init_controls.lua:467` |\n\n### Risks\n1. **Port ref table keys**: `portRef.nodeId` is used extensively - need to ensure we only rename rack-module contexts, not DSP graph node refs\n2. **External API calls**: My files call `spliceNode`, `cloneNodes`, `findNodeIndex`, `makeConnectionDescriptor` which are owned by other workers - they'll break until those workers complete\n3. **State shape**: `ctx._rackState.nodes` → `ctx._rackState.modules` is a schema change that affects runtime state\n\n### First Steps (Pending GO)\n1. Rename `_rackNodeSpecs` → `_rackModuleSpecs` in my files (local state)\n2. Rename `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` → `RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT` references\n3. Rename `rackState.nodes` → `rackState.modules` and `ctx._rackState.nodes` → `ctx._rackState.modules`\n4. Rename connection endpoint refs: `from.nodeId`/`to.nodeId` → `from.moduleId`/`to.moduleId`\n5. Rename `portRef.nodeId` → `portRef.moduleId` in rack module contexts\n6. Update external API calls to new names (will be broken until other workers finish)\n7. `luac -p` each file, `rg` verify no old symbols remain\n\n**Ready for GO signal.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-codin