{"type":"message","id":"b9ff02d7","parentId":"7ba0ebfa","timestamp":"2026-04-02T18:12:12.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All done. Now let me provide the final report.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Final Report: Worker C (Patchbay / Wire Migration)\n\n### Files Changed (6 files)\n| File | Lines Changed | Key Renames |\n|------|---------------|-------------|\n| `ui/behaviors/rack_wire_layer.lua` | ~50 | `nodeId`→`moduleId` in port refs, `nodes`→`modules`, `spliceNode`→`spliceRackModule` (call), `getNodeRow`→`getModuleRow` |\n| `lib/ui/patchbay_generator.lua` | ~40 | `_rackNodeSpecs`→`_rackModuleSpecs`, `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT`→`RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT`, `nodeId`→`moduleId` in port entries, `rackState.nodes`→`rackState.modules` |\n| `lib/ui/patchbay_runtime.lua` | ~45 | `_rackNodeSpecs`→`_rackModuleSpecs`, `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT`→`RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT`, `cloneNodes`→`cloneRackModules` (call), `findNodeIndex`→`findRackModuleIndex` (call), `nodeId`→`moduleId` in params, `nodes`→`modules` |\n| `ui/components/patchbay_panel.lua` | 0 | No changes required |\n| `lib/ui/rack_mod_popover.lua` | ~25 | `_rackNodeSpecs`→`_rackModuleSpecs`, `portRef.nodeId`→`portRef.moduleId`, `conn.from.nodeId`→`conn.from.moduleId`, `conn.to.nodeId`→`conn.to.moduleId`, `entry.nodeId`→`entry.moduleId` |\n| `lib/ui/init_controls.lua` | ~5 | `makeConnectionDescriptor`→`makeRackConnection` (call), `ctx._rackState.nodes`→`ctx._rackState.modules` |\n\n### Exact Renames Completed\n**Table field/key renames:**\n- `portRef.nodeId` → `portRef.moduleId` (in shallowCopyPortRef, portAnchorsCompatible, findPortEntry)\n- `conn.from.nodeId` → `conn.from.moduleId`\n- `conn.to.nodeId` → `conn.to.moduleId`\n- `entry.nodeId` → `entry.moduleId` (port registry comparisons)\n- `candidate.nodeId` → `candidate.moduleId`\n\n**State/schema renames:**\n- `ctx._rackState.nodes` → `ctx._rackState.modules`\n- `rackState.nodes` → `rackState.modules`\n- `_rackNodeSpecs` → `_rackModuleSpecs`\n\n**External API calls (updated to new names):**\n- `MidiSynthRackSpecs.spliceNode()` → `MidiSynthRackSpecs.spliceRackModule()`\n- `RackLayout.cloneNodes()` → `RackLayout.cloneRackModules()`\n- `RackLayout.findNodeIndex()` → `RackLayout.findRackModuleIndex()`\n- `RackLayout.makeConnectionDescriptor()` → `RackLayout.makeRackConnection()`\n\n**Layout map renames:**\n- `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` → `RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT` (in my function parameters and references)\n\n### Unresolved Dependencies on Other Workers\n| Symbol | Owner | Status |\n|--------|-------|--------|\n| `MidiSynthRackSpecs.spliceRackModule()` | Worker B | Function owned by Worker B; my call site updated |\n| `RackLayout.cloneRackModules()` | Worker A | Function owned by Worker A; my call site updated |\n| `RackLayout.findRackModuleIndex()` | Worker A | Function owned by Worker A; my call site updated |\n| `RackLayout.makeRackConnection()` | Worker A | Function owned by Worker A; my call site updated |\n| `RackLayout.moveNodeToSlot()` | Worker A | **NOT in contract** - kept original name |\n| `RackLayout.getFlowNodes()` | Worker A | **NOT in contract** - kept original name |\n| `deps.RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT` | Worker D | Worker D must update their code to pass this key |\n\n### Risks\n1. **Cross-worker API breakage**: My files call external APIs (`spliceRackModule`, `cloneRackModules`, `findRackModuleIndex`, `makeRackConnection`) that other workers must rename. If they don't complete their renames, my code will fail at runtime.\n\n2. **Port registry compatibility**: The port entry table structure now uses `moduleId` field. Any code (including other workers) that reads `entry.nodeId` from port registry entries will break until they update to `entry.moduleId`.\n\n3. **Connection shape compatibility**: Connection endpoint tables now use `moduleId` instead of `nodeId`. Other workers that access `conn.from.nodeId` or `conn.to.nodeId` must update to `.moduleId`.\n\n### Verification\n- ✅ All 6 files pass `luac -p` syntax check\n- ✅ No old symbols (`_rackNodeSpecs`, `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` as global ref, `from.nodeId`, `to.nodeId`, etc.) remain in owned files\n- ✅ Function parameters and local variables intentionally retain `nodeId` naming (not table fields)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding-plan","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":113,"output":1104,"cacheRead":103424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104641,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775153507844,"responseId":"msg_QXN4BYyLOQyYz7T8MrP6vF5a"}}
